        <p>
            A log is an operation that combines two numbers to make a new number. The log operation combines the base and a target, and gives us back the exponent that we need to raise the base to to get the target. Just like when you learned the <q>raise to the power of</q> operation in a previous math class, practice is the key to feeling comfortable with this new operation. 
        </p>
